title: Princeton graduate student abducted in Iraq by Iran-linked militia
description: Elizabeth Tsurkov was conducting doctoral research in Baghdad when she went missing in March.

title: Yan Mingfu, Chinese official demoted after Tiananmen crackdown, dies at 91
description: He led the government outreach to the Tiananmen protesters and once offered himself as a "hostage" for protesters on hunger strike.

title: King Charles is (again) presented with a crown. This time in Scotland.
description: King Charles III was presented with Scotland's crown jewels, which are even older than England's, in an important ceremony reaffirming Great Britain's union.

title: Tracing a tragedy: How hundreds of migrants drowned on Greece’s watch
description: A Washington Post investigation retraced the route of the Adriana and how Greek coast guard decisions contributed to a preventable tragedy.

title: Kremlin warns of ‘sabotage’ at Ukrainian nuclear plant under Russian control
description: Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov said that Ukraine would sabotage Europe's biggest atomic power plant. Ukraine has warned for weeks that Russia is planning a radioactive disaster.

title: Two decades ago, Bill Clinton threw a Hail Mary for Middle East peace
description: President Bill Clinton brought Israeli and Palestinian leaders to Camp David in July 2000, seeking peace and a legacy for himself. Then it all collapsed.

title: Israel’s raid left Jenin in rubble. Netanyahu says it won’t be the last time.
description: As the residents of Jenin camp rebuild from the two-day raid that killed 12, a new Israeli response to West Bank militancy is emerging featuring longer, bloodier operations.

title: Hate packing clothes for vacation? Japan-bound travelers may not have to.
description: Japan Airlines' new clothing rental program aims to cut carbon emissions and appeal to passengers who have become accustomed to the sharing economy.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Swedish leader in D.C. amid NATO bid; Kyiv, Moscow trade false-flag claims on nuclear plant
description: During the White House visit, Swedish Prime Minister Ulf Kristersson and President Biden are set to discuss support for Ukraine and Sweden’s bid to join NATO.

title: What does the Barbie movie have to do with the South China Sea dispute?
description: Vietnam banned screenings of the upcoming Barbie film over a map that appears to depict Beijing’s disputed “nine-dash line” claim in the South China Sea.

title: Wagner rebellion raises doubts about stability of Russia’s nuclear arsenal
description: Western nations long viewed Vladimir Putin as a steady hand in control of Russia’s nuclear arsenal, but heated rhetoric about a strike on NATO suggests that may no longer be true.

title: New Zealand’s bind: Balancing Western security against Chinese trade
description: New Zealand has so far managed to avoid China's economic retaliation for political decisions. That could change if it's asked to join phase two of the AUKUS pact.

title: France’s riots create opening for the far right
description: Various luminaries of the French establishment have argued that France’s secular, republican ethos are getting corroded by a leftist, “identitarian” streak.

title: Léon Gautier, French commando who landed at Normandy, dies at 100
description: “The younger generations have to be told,” Mr. Gautier said. "War is ugly. War is misery, misery everywhere.”
